From: b70 torch-xpu fix (2026-07-07)
Subject: [PATCH] [XPU] XPUGraph::replay: use submit_without_event to stop per-replay
 Level-Zero command-list leak

at::xpu::XPUGraphImpl::replay() submits the captured SYCL command_graph via
queue.ext_oneapi_graph(), which routes through submit_with_event. Each replay
allocates a host-visible sycl::event that pins the in-order queue's Level-Zero
immediate-command-list segment until the UR adapter cleanup pass runs. Under
repeated replay (speculative decoding replays the drafter graph thousands of
times with no full teardown) the command buffer grows unbounded until NEO
LinearStream::getSpace aborts (linear_stream.h:84). submit_without_event skips
the per-submit event so the in-order queue recycles its command-list space each
replay.

Applies to pytorch @ 7661cd9c6b841b62b7f411aa52ec51f05457263b (torch 2.12.0+xpu).

Note: queue.submit_without_event(...) is a PRIVATE internal template on sycl::queue, so the fix
uses the PUBLIC event-less free function sycl::ext::oneapi::experimental::execute_graph(queue, G)
(from enqueue_functions.hpp), which routes through the same event-less submit(). `using namespace
sycl::ext::oneapi::experimental` is already in scope at the top of XPUGraph.cpp.

--- a/aten/src/ATen/xpu/XPUGraph.cpp
+++ b/aten/src/ATen/xpu/XPUGraph.cpp
@@ void XPUGraphImpl::replay() {
   auto& queue = at::xpu::getCurrentXPUStream().queue();
-  queue.ext_oneapi_graph(*graph_exec_);
+  // B70 fix (2026-07-07): queue.ext_oneapi_graph() routes through submit_with_event, allocating a
+  // per-replay sycl::event that pins the in-order queue's Level-Zero immediate-command-list segment
+  // until the UR adapter cleanup pass runs. Under repeated replay (e.g. speculative decoding replays
+  // the drafter graph thousands of times) the command buffer grows unbounded -> NEO
+  // LinearStream::getSpace overflow (linear_stream.h:84 abort). The public execute_graph() free
+  // function routes through the EVENT-LESS submit(), so no per-replay event is created and the
+  // in-order queue recycles its command-list space each replay.
+  execute_graph(queue, *graph_exec_);
 }
